Title: Object: Ruins of the Ptolomean Library
Series: Views in Egypt, Palestine and other parts of the Ottoman Empire
Description: Plate 18 in volume I: in the left foreground, four men with turbans resting next to large blocks on the ground, a woman with a blue veil passing by; behind them, more blocks underneath a hill on which a shepherd standing; men rowing two boats on the right; after Mayer; published state. 1802 Hand-coloured aquatint with etching
Bibliographic references: Abbey Travel / Travel in Aquatint and lithography 1770-1860 from the library of J.R.Abbey (369.I.18)
